Class AbstractDialogComponentRangeInput<T extends javax.swing.JComponent & Changeable,M extends org.knime.core.node.defaultnodesettings.SettingsModel & SettingsModelComparableRangeBounded<U>,U extends java.lang.Comparable<U>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.defaultnodesettings.DialogComponent
      • com.vernalis.pdbconnector2.dialogcomponents.AbstractDialogComponentRangeInput<T,M,U>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the min/max dialog components
    M - The type of the SettingsModel
    U - The type of the component value stored in the model
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DialogComponentDateRangeInput, DialogComponentDoubleRangeBounded, DialogComponentIntRangeBounded

    public abstract class AbstractDialogComponentRangeInput<T extends javax.swing.JComponent & Changeable,M extends org.knime.core.node.defaultnodesettings.SettingsModel & SettingsModelComparableRangeBounded<U>,U extends java.lang.Comparable<U>>
extends org.knime.core.node.defaultnodesettings.DialogComponent
    A DialogComponent to input a data range via two data entry components. The range is bounded, with the bounds determined in the SettingsModelComparableRangeBounded supplied
    Since:
    1.28.0
    Author:
    S.Roughley knime@vernalis.com

    • Method Detail

      • updateMinModel

        protected void updateMinModel()
        This method is called by a change to the min component value. The default implementation sets the lower value of the settings model, and sets the max component's minimum bound to this value. An error is shown in the min component in the UI if an exception was thrown

      • updateMaxModel

        protected void updateMaxModel()
        This method is called by a change to the max component value. The default implementation sets the upper value of the settings model, and sets the min component's maximum bound to this value. An error is shown in the max component in the UI if an exception was thrown
